The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 1: Air India will start operations at its first international hub in Frankfurt by the end of this month. The airline will launch scissor operations to and from North America with a new fleet of Boeing aircraft. It will take about 19 hours, including the changeover time at Frankfurt, for a passenger to reach the US cities from India.                            
	 New Delhi, March 1: Sugar output in India may slump 39 per cent to 16 million tonnes this season, prompting the country to import a projected 1.5 million tonnes, according to the Indian Sugar Mills Association. The decline in output is because of less cane crop and a lower rate of sugar production out of cane.                            
	 New Delhi, March 1: Indian equities have given the worst returns to investors in February compared with their peers in the three other BRIC nations  Brazil, Russia and China. Stocks on the Indian bourses yielded a negative return of 10.40 per cent last month.                            
	 Mumbai, March 1: Standard Chartered has no plans to freeze hiring in India despite the challenging market conditions. The bank will recruit around 2,000 professionals this year. It recruited 4,000 people in the last calendar year.                             
	 New Delhi, March 1: The government plans to invest up to Rs 2,500 crore, with a similar amount from private players, for promoting research and development in pharma.                                                                                                                            
